    "description":  "Find out how to access additional support services including those from the existing Infected Blood support schemes, charities and NHS. ",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eThere is support available for those infected and affected through the Infected Blood Support Schemes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eThe \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.sibps.scot.nhs.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eScottish Infected Blood Psychology Service\u003c/a\u003e supports people who contracted Hepatitis C and / or HIV from blood and/or blood products given during medical procedures in Scotland.\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eThe \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/england-infected-blood-support-scheme\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eEngland Infected Blood Support Scheme\u003c/a\u003e offers discretionary payments to fund independent psychology therapies for the existing beneficiaries, their families and friends. \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eIn Wales, there is the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://wibss.wales.nhs.uk/the-psychology-wellbeing-service/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ePsychology \u0026amp; Wellbeing Service\u003c/a\u003e, where persons registered with the Wales Infected Blood Support Scheme, their family members and bereaved family members can access psychological assessment and treatment concerning the emotional difficulties of being given and living with a diagnosis of Hepatitis C and/or HIV. \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eIn Northern Ireland, there is a dedicated regional specialist psychological service delivered within the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://belfasttrust.hscni.net/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eBelfast Health and Social Care Trust\u003c/a\u003e for persons aged 18 years and above who have been infected and affected as a result of receiving contaminated blood. The service is also for family members and provides social work support. For more information, please call 028 9615 5867.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"hiv-support\"\u003eHIV support \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eThe Terrence Higgins Trust (THT) provides resources for people living with HIV and those newly diagnosed. You can contact THT for support, advice and information by telephone on 0808 802 1221 or by email at \u003ca href=\"mailto:info@tht.org.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003einfo@tht.org.uk\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ePositively UK provides peer-led support, advocacy and information to everyone living with HIV to effectively manage any aspect of their diagnosis, care and life with HIV. You can contact them by telephone on 0207 7713 044 or by email at \u003ca href=\"mailto:info@positivelyuk.org\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003einfo@positivelyuk.org\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"hepatitis-c-support\"\u003eHepatitis C support\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eThe Hepatitis C Trust is a patient-led and patient-run organisation. There is a confidential national telephone helpline service on 020 7089 6221 or you can email them at \u003ca href=\"mailto:helpline@hepctrust.org.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ehelpline@hepctrust.org.uk\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"haemophilia-support\"\u003eHaemophilia support\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eHaemophilia support is a UK-wide charity for all those affected by a genetic bleeding disorder - a community of individuals and families, healthcare professionals and supporters. You can contact them by telephone on 020 7939 0780 or by email \u003ca href=\"mailto:info@haemophilia.org.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003einfo@haemophilia.org.uk\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"bereavement-support\"\u003eBereavement support\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eCruse Bereavement Care is a national charity for bereaved people in England, Wales and Northern Ireland. You can contact their telephone helpline on 0808 808 1677. \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eBereavement UK provides bereavement support and information. You can contact them by email at \u003ca href=\"mailto:support@bereavement.co.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003esupport@bereavement.co.uk\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"nhs-england\"\u003eNHS England \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNHS England has a \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://nhs.uk/infected-blood-support\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ededicated support page for people who may have been affected by infected blood\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"nhs-blood-and-transplant\"\u003eNHS Blood and Transplant \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you have any concerns about current blood donation or transfusions, you can find out more about \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nhsbt.nhs.uk/what-we-do/blood-services/blood-transfusion/transfusion-faqs/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eblood transfusions on the NHS Blood and Transplant website\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"financial-support\"\u003eFinancial Support\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFree, impartial financial support is available through \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.moneyhelper.org.uk/en\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eMoneyHelper\u003c/a\u003e and the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCitizens Advice Service\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"other-support-groups\"\u003eOther support groups\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are several independent support groups that are sign posted to via the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.infectedbloodinquiry.org.uk/psychological-support-provided-inquiry/support-groups\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eInfected Blood Inquiry’s website\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
